<subSubSection id="CCC31591D732FF9FFF7BA9D3DEFC41B1" pageId="61" pageNumber="1400" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8466461AD732FF9FFF7BA9D3DEFC41B1" blockId="61.[178,1086,213,981]" pageId="61" pageNumber="1400">
Comments: The aedeagal characters illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="E0483BEBD732FF9FFD1AA9D3DE59408D" author="LOBL I." box="[723,854,723,745]" journalOrPublisher="Mitt. Schweiz. ent. Ges." pageId="61" pageNumber="1400" pagination="125 - 132" part="43" refString="LOBL I. (1970 a): Uber einige Scaphidiidae (Coleoptera) aus der Sammlung des Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris. - Mitt. Schweiz. ent. Ges. 43: 125 - 132." title="Uber einige Scaphidiidae (Coleoptera) aus der Sammlung des Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle de Paris" type="journal article" year="1970" yearSuffix="a">LÖBL 1970a</bibRefCitation>
: 127 were taken from the sole specimen available at that time, a male with partly extruded internal sac, and lack in detail. Therefore, new illustrations are given in the present work (
<figureCitation id="1CE25A9FD732FF9FFC69A808D93E4141" box="[928,1073,783,805]" captionStart="Figs 142 - 145" captionStartId="133.[178,218,1311,1333]" captionTargetBox="[219,1071,215,1269]" captionTargetId="figure@133.[178,1085,212,1301]" captionTargetPageId="133" captionText="Figs 142 - 145: Aedeagi of Scaphisoma in dorsal and lateral views; (142, 143), S. bicoloripenne nov. sp., scale = 0.2 mm; (144, 145) S. biplagiatum HELLER, scale = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/247222/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="1400">Figs 144, 145</figureCitation>
). The species is a member of the 
<emphasis id="B6AD9A08D732FF9FFE33A82BDF554126" box="[506,602,812,834]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="1400">S. pictum</emphasis>
group, characterized by the internal sac with a large basal tuft of spines joined with a large basal tooth, in combination with a large apical denticle and a subrectangular or subpentagonal central sclerite. The aedeagal characters suggest close relationship with 
<emphasis id="B6AD9A08D732FF9FFDB8A883DFED41FD" box="[625,738,900,921]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="1400">S. dohertyi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="E0483BEBD732FF9FFD24A883DE5A41FE" author="PIC M." box="[749,853,900,922]" journalOrPublisher="Melang. exot. - ent" pageId="61" pageNumber="1400" pagination="2 - 13" part="16" refString="PIC M. (1915): Genres nouveaux. Especes et varietes nouvelles. - Melang. exot. - ent. 16: 2 - 13." title="Genres nouveaux. Especes et varietes nouvelles" type="journal article" year="1915">PIC, 1915</bibRefCitation>
, widely distributed in tropical Asia. The basal bulb of the median lobe is extended in S. 
<emphasis id="B6AD9A08D732FF9FFC9DA8A6DEA741D2" box="[852,936,929,950]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="1400">dohertyi</emphasis>
, unlike that in 
<emphasis id="B6AD9A08D732FF9FFF7BA8B8DC4A41B0" box="[178,325,959,980]" italics="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="1400">S. biplagiatum</emphasis>
, and completely overlapping the apical process of the median lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
